A whopping 94 percent of TSSA members voted in favour of the pay rise, which will be backdated to the first Sunday in April 2022. Manuel Cortes, the head of the Transport Salaried Staffs' Association (TSSA) union said in a statement following the Merseyrail deal: "What this clearly shows is our union, and sister unions, are in no way a block on finding the solutions needed to avoid a summer of discontent on the railways." Train strikes are expected to continue across the country on Thursday and Saturday as the RMT union battles for a seven percent pay rise for rail workers. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES... 